                        <div>
                            <h2>One of the world's best student cities</h2>
                            <p>Want to study in an exciting multicultural city? You won't be disappointed in London. With more international students choosing London than any other city, you won't be alone.&nbsp;</p>
                            <p>It's England's capital - one of the busiest and most exciting cities in the UK. But it's not all concrete and buildings! 30% of London is open space and there are over 140 parks and gardens to choose from.&nbsp;</p>
                            <p>Whether you want to visit one of the 90 museums and galleries, see one of the 200 attractions, go to a festival, a football match or a musical, there's always something to do in London.</p>
                            <a class="l-cta cta" href="/en/study-programs">Find a course in London</a>
                            <p></p>
                            <h2>What makes London unique?</h2>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Top 3 best student city in the world (QS Best Student Cities 2014).</li>
                                <li>Home to 18 of the world's best universities.</li>
                                <li>A huge student population - 380,000 students live here, including 100,000 international students.</li>
                                <li>One of the greenest capital cities in the world, with over 3,000 parks and open spaces.&nbsp;</li>
                                <li>A global capital of culture, with 200+ museums and galleries and 200 live music performances a day.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
