                        <div>
                            <h2>Food in London</h2>
                            <p>From Chinese to Italian, French to Indian, Lebanese to Korean, there are thousands of restaurants, markets, street stalls and cafés of all price ranges that reflect the city’s multicultural population.</p>
                            <p>Head to Chinatown for a wide selection of Chinese restaurants, Brick Lane for a curry or Southall for Caribbean cuisine.</p>
                            <p>Of course, don’t forget to enjoy some of the UK’s specialties like fish and chips or a traditional roast dinner in a cosy pub.</p>
                            <p></p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
        </div>
        <div class="DnnModule-DNN_HTML DnnVersionableControl">
            <section class="l-page-block l-text-block bottom-line">
                <div class="l-content-container">
                    <div class="DNNModuleContent ModDNNHTMLC">
                        <div>
                            <h2>London's main attractions</h2>
                            <p>With four World Heritage sites and hundreds of world famous attractions, you won’t ever be bored in London. Here are some of the best bits:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Tower of London</li>
                                <li>London Eye</li>
                                <li>Big Ben</li>
                                <li>Houses of Parliament</li>
                                <li>St Paul’s Cathedral</li>
                                <li>Westminster Abbey</li>
                                <li>National Gallery</li>
                                <li>Buckingham Palace</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h2>Managing your money</h2>
                            <p>After your first few weeks in London, you'll have a good idea of how much things cost. To help with this, the table below outlines an estimated monthly budget (excluding tuition and accommodation fees), as an indication.</p>
                            <table class="r-tbl-headers" style="width: 100%;">
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th style="width: 70%;">
                                            <strong>Item</strong>
                                        </th>
                                        <th style="width: 30%;">
                                            <strong>Cost per month</strong>
                                        </th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td data-header="Item" class="v-top">
                                            Food
                                        </td>
                                        <td data-header="Cost per month" class="v-top">
                                            £250
                                        </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td data-header="Item" class="v-top">
